claim.claim-text:
19. An apparatus for forming polycrystalline silicon from amorphous silicon comprising: 
a first energy source emitting an energy beam; 
a beam splitter configured to split the energy beam into a first part and a second part; 
a first delivery element configured to deliver the first part to a position on the amorphous silicon film for a first duration; and 
a second delivery element configured to deliver the second part to the position for a second duration superpositioned with the first duration.

21. An apparatus for forming polycrystalline silicon from amorphous silicon comprising: 
a first energy source emitting a first energy beam; 
a second energy source emitting a second energy beam; 
a first delivery element configured to deliver the first beam to a position on the amorphous silicon film for a first duration; and 
a second delivery element configured to deliver the second beam to the position after the first beam and for a second duration superpositioned within the first duration.

23. An apparatus comprising: 
a first energy source emitting a first energy beam; 
a second energy source emitting a second energy beam; 
a delivery element configured to deliver the first beam to a position on a layer of material in a first physical state; 
a controller in communication with the first energy source and the second energy source; and 
a memory coupled to said controller, said memory storing a computer program in computer readable format including computer instructions to control said controller to, 
a. cause the first energy beam to be applied to the position at a first time and for a first duration, and 
b. cause the second second energy beam to be applied to the position for a second time and for a second duration, the second time subsequent to the first time and the second duration expiring on or before the first duration, such that the layer of material is converted from the first state to a second state.
